  "texts": [
    "As it turns out, they already yield surprising results when applied to near-term QML models employing quantum states as inputs.",
    "Our empirical findings, also in the form of numerical experiments, reveal that uniform generalization bounds may not be the right approach for current-scale QML.",
    "To corroborate this body of numerical work with a rigorous underpinning, we show how QML models can assign arbitrary labels to quantum states.",
    "Specifically, we show that PQCs are able to perfectly fit training sets of polynomial size in the number of qubits.",
    "By revealing this ability to memorize random data, our results rule out the good generalization guarantees with few training data from uniform bounds 54,58."
